   "kind": 2,
   "value": "SolveP0[Func_] := Block[\r\n    {x, y, z},\r\n    (*\r\n    given a func defined as a*x + b*y + c*z + d it must be equal to 0. \r\n    a or b or c or d can be 0 but neither of a, b and c must not be 0.\r\n    \r\n    *)\r\n\r\n\r\n    {x, y, z}\r\n]\r\n\r\n(* Define the projection function *)\r\nSolveOPinPlane[Func_, P_] := Block[ (*without P0. Func in progress*)\r\n    {u, proj, P1, n, P0},\r\n    \r\n    (* Step 1: Get the n vector to the plane (coefficients of the plane equation) *)\r\n    n = Grad[Func[x, y, z], {x, y, z}];  (* Gradients give the n vector *)\r\n    (* working *)\r\n    \r\n    (* Step 2: Choose an arbitrary point on the plane (P0). Let's solve Func = 0 for P0. *)\r\n    Solve[Func[]]\r\n    P0 = {x, y, z} /. Solve[Func[x, y, z] == 0, {x, y, z}][[1]];  (* Find a point on the plane *)\r\n    \r\n    (* Step 3: Calculate vector u = P0 - P *)\r\n    u = P0 - P;\r\n    \r\n    (* Step 4: Project u onto the n vector to get the displacement to the plane *)\r\n    proj = Projection[u, n];\r\n    \r\n    (* Step 5: Calculate the new point P1 on the plane *)\r\n    P1 = P + proj;\r\n    \r\n    (* Return the projected point *)\r\n    P1\r\n]",
